getDefaultCharacterSet

public static Charset getDefaultCharacterSet()
Return the default character set, which is UTF-8, but could in principle change.

Returns:
a static Charset object

charsetFromString

public static Charset charsetFromString(java.lang.String charsetName)
Converts a character set name to a Charset. If the input name is null, then return the default Charset. If the input name does not correspond to a legal or supported character set, then return the default Charset and give a warning.

Parameters:
charsetName - the name of a putative character set, or null
Returns:
the Charset corresponding to the argument, or the default character set (see getDefaultCharacterSet()) if that is not possible
